name: 3-isopropylmalate dehydrogenase
classes: Acting on the CH-OH group of donors;
With NAD+ or NADP+ as acceptor
reaction: (2R,3S)-3-isopropylmalate + NAD+ = 4-methyl-2-oxopentanoate + CO2 + NADH + H+ (overall reaction) [RN:R10052]; (1a) (2R,3S)-3-isopropylmalate + NAD+ = (2S)-2-isopropyl-3-oxosuccinate + NADH + H+ [RN:R04426]; (1b) (2S)-2-isopropyl-3-oxosuccinate = 4-methyl-2-oxopentanoate + CO2 (spontaneous) [RN:R01652]
comment: The product decarboxylates spontaneously to yield 4-methyl-2-oxopentanoate.
